commit.message: Explcitly list AVX512 forms without the optional {er}/{sae} operands
Explicitly specify CMPXCHG8B/CMPXCHG16B extensions
Add LAHF and SAHF instructions in 64-bit mode

Remove 64-bit TBM instructions from 32-bit x86 ISA

These instructions can't be encoded in 32-bit x86 and were added by
mistake
Fix operand types in UMONITOR instruction
Add CET-IBT extension
Add RDFSBASE, RDGSBASE, WRFSBASE, WRGSBASE instructions
Fix AT&T assembly name for XLATB instructions
Fix operand types in MOVDIR64B instruction
Add MOVDIRI and MOVDIR64B instructions
Add MCOMMIT instruction
Add CLDEMOTE instruction

Add WAITPKG instruction set

Add UMONITOR, UMWAIT, and TPAUSE instructions
Add SERIALIZE instruction

Change operand type for PREFETCHIT0/PREFETCHIT1 instructions

PREFETCHIT0/PREFETCHIT1 instructions per Intel manual accept an m8
operand. However, this m8 operand is restricted to RIP-relative address,
similar to rel32, although it is encoded via Mod R/M byte rather than
via immediate 32-bit relative offset. This change introduced a new
rel32m operand type specifically for this instruction. Unfortunately, we
can't directly use rel32, because the assembly syntax is different, e.g.
offset(%rip) instead of offset in AT&T assembly.
Add RDRPU instruction
Add RDPID instruction
Add RDPMC instruction

Remove l/q suffix from gas mnemonics for BSWAP

GAS prefers suffix-less mnemonics and produce them on disassembly

Split masked operands into explicitly masked and unmasked forms

Some instructions (gather, scatter, and corresponding prefetch
instructions) have only masked forms, but the specification didn't
indicate it in any form. Making unmasked forms explicit exposes
this information.
Add GitHub Action to validate XML against XSD schemas

Remove zero-masked memory operands

Zero-masking is supported only for register operands, and these forms
were added by mistake.
Fix x86-64 XSD schema
Fix position of {er} operand adjacent to r32/m32 or r64/m64 operands

Add INT3 instructions

Previously it was a specialization of `INT 3`, but behaviour is slightly
different than the two-byte INT instruction and Intel manuals consider
it a separate instruction
Fix AT&T name for MOV r64, imm64 instruction
Fix specification of [V]PCMPESTRI/[V]PCMPESTRM instructions
Fix AT&T names for some SIMD instructions
Fix AT&T names for some scalar conversion instructions
Fix AT&T names for some general-purpose instructions
